# Refactoring & Type Tightening

## File Split Pattern

When a file exceeds the size cap, follow the **barrel + delegation** pattern:

1. **Keep the original file as a barrel**: it retains the class shell (thin methods) and re-exports.
2. **Extract logic into submodules**: each new file exports standalone functions that take the necessary state as parameters.
3. **Zero churn for consumers**: every existing import continues to point at the original file.

```typescript
// agent-session.ts (barrel) — retains the class, delegates to submodules
import { runManualCompaction } from "./agent-session-compaction.js";

class AgentSession {
	async compact() {
		return runManualCompaction(this.agent, this.sessionManager, ...);
	}
}

export { AgentSession };
export * from "./agent-session-types.js";
```

### Post-Split Checklist

- [ ] The barrel re-exports every public API
- [ ] Submodules have no circular dependencies
- [ ] `tsgo --noEmit` (or equivalent) passes
- [ ] No duplicate functions (extraction commonly produces them)
- [ ] Delegation methods avoid `as any`; if unavoidable, define a shared Host interface

