## Phase 3: Gradual `any` Tightening

Biome's `noExplicitAny` is set to `warn`. Tighten in this order:

### Priority 1 — Cross-package public APIs (one batch already done)

- `evo-session` Hub client: `HubAsset`, `HubFetchResponse`, `HubPublishResult`
- `agent-core` evolution hooks: removed `(m as any).isError`
- `extensions/loader.ts`: `ExtensionFactory` is now typed

### Priority 2 — `interactive-mode.ts` delegation interface

Currently 32 instances of `this as any` are passed to submodules. Define:

```typescript
interface InteractiveModeHost {
	readonly session: AgentSession;
	readonly chatContainer: Container;
	// ...
}
```

All submodules consume `InteractiveModeHost` instead of `any`.

### Priority 3 — Provider-layer API responses

Use the OpenAI / Anthropic / Google SDK's own types to replace `any` responses in the provider layer.

### Priority 4 — web-ui Lark callbacks

Type the callbacks in web-ui that interact with external APIs.

### Standard for new code

- New code does not introduce new `any` unless protected by a TypeBox schema or runtime type check.
- PR review check: total `any` count must not increase.

## Large-File Prevention Strategy

The hard cap lives in `clean-code-core.mdc#structural-constraints` (500 lines). Repo-level CI / review additions:

- A `wc -l` check in CI: `find packages/*/src -name '*.ts' ! -name '*.generated.ts' | xargs wc -l | awk '$1 > 500 { print "WARN:", $0 }'`
- During feature development, if you estimate > 300 lines, plan the split up front.
- During code review, watch single-file size; any change crossing 500 lines requires a split plan.

## Test-Coverage Strategy

All Vitest packages have v8 coverage configured (`vitest.config.ts`):

- `ai`, `agent`, `coding-agent`, `evo-session`: `include: ["src/**/*.ts"]`, `exclude: ["**/*.generated.ts"]`
- `tui`: `include: ["src/**/*.ts"]`
- `web-ui`: `include: ["src/**/*.ts"]`, environment: `happy-dom`

Run coverage: `npm run test:coverage`.

Phase targets:

1. Collect baseline data first (current coverage).
2. Core modules (agent-core, ai, evo-session) target 60%+.
3. coding-agent targets 40%+ (TUI / CLI interactions are hard to unit-test).
4. web-ui targets 30%+ (DOM-environment limits).
